Crotona Park is a public park in the South Bronx section of the Bronx, New York City, covering 127.5 acres (0.516 km2; 0.1992 sq mi). The park is bounded by streets of the same name on its northern, eastern, southern, and western borders. It is divided into four portions by Claremont Parkway and Crotona Avenue, which run through it. Crotona Park formerly belonged to the Bathgate family.